            <li>Tokenizes sports field sections as coordinate-based NFTs fans can own</li>
            <li>Fans earn rewards when real match events occur at their owned coordinates</li>
            <li>Supports football, chess, tennis, and cricket with sport-specific coordinate systems</li>
            <li>Generates new revenue streams for clubs beyond tickets and merchandise</li>
            <li>Increases live match engagement as fans track action across owned field sections</li>
          </ul>
        </div>
        <h3><strong>Club Revenue Stream Creation</strong></h3>
        <p>
          These engagement mechanics translate directly into revenue opportunities for sports clubs. Clubs generate income through initial NFT sales of field coordinate sections, with fans actively purchasing ownership of premium field locations where significant action frequently occurs.
        </p>
        <p>
          The revenue potential extends beyond initial sales. Secondary market trading creates ongoing engagement as fans buy and sell coordinate sections based on performance and anticipated value. Clubs can configure royalties on these secondary sales, establishing continuous revenue streams that grow with platform activity.
        </p>
        <p>
          Furthermore, the platform enables strategic pricing through tiered ownership. Premium sections command higher prices based on game dynamics—corner kick areas in football or service boxes in tennis become high-value assets. This creates diverse price points that maximize both accessibility and revenue optimization.
        </p>

